Bolivia Bank Approves $118 Million Lithium Loan, La Razon Says

-- B y   S a r a   S h a h r i a r i
-- 
2011-05-13T15:52:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-13/bolivia-bank-approves-118-million-lithium-loan-la-razon-says.html
Bolivia ’s  Central Bank  will loan $118
million to Bolivia’s state mining company Corporacion Minera de
Bolivia, or COMIBOL, for lithium production, La Paz-based daily
La Razon reported.  The loan is approved by the central bank and a contract may
be signed within days, La Razon said, citing Mining Minister
Jose Pimentel. The majority of the loan will be used to develop
production of  lithium carbonate  and potassium chloride, while $5
million will be invested in developing lithium batteries, La
Razon said. The government plans to invest about $400 million in
total in the lithium project, La Razon said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sara Shahriari in La Paz at 
 sshahriari@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts in  Buenos Aires  at 
 dcrofts@bloomberg.net  